values:
So after sort of finishing the physics I needed to get done for tuesday (with stellar answers like "hot as balls" in response to being asked to describe in a meaningful manner how hot the sun is) and finishing my Celtic reflection paper (with stories of an irish dancing sister, two brawls with IRA members in Ireland, and plans for a tatoo I never intend on getting) I feel a little better. 

But there still lies two major (10 page) research papers. Two Finals and a report for my internship. Considering how hard I"ve been working to get things done, this just looks exhausting. I don't know if it's just the graduating thing, or the stress of 50% of my grades depending on how I do over the course of two weeks while still trying to be a decent boyfriend, friend, son, and sane. I've done ok, but I know thats not really close to good, or where I should be right now. I am really really afraid of this mentality coming back. The last thing in the world that I want right now is being back on medicine. 

I did finally get my acceptance letter from UofL now. Not that I needed to be concerned, it is UofL. But that is set now, so I can do whatever I need to do for that. I got invited to the awards ceremony for school, for what I don't know. Besides running, working and class (if I go), those are the only obligations I have this week. Hopefully that means I'll have enough time for the projects and a date or two. 

Next wednesday, 9 people will be coming to crash my house in celebration for Derby. I have a final the day after, lol! It should be a lot of fun, and I'm really looking forward to seeing them for the first time in a year. That, I think more than anything is what is carrying me through these last two papers and finals. 

I always feel like there is something else I meant to write about. But now I can't remember what it was supposed to be. I don't have any deep insights. I just want to get lots of sleep, curled under my blankets, and not to have a headache for a bit. That would be fantastic. :-)

5.5 days until the marathon, and 10 until people come. I'm so glad that I'm getting to graduate!

1.) I have the cutest little sister ever 

2.) I absolutely HATE these papers 

3.) I might have just written the worst one all semester, worth 20% of my grade.  

4.) I downloaded pacman for my ipod, very exciting! 

sister is distracting me, I'm not doing any more work on papers today.

PS. 5.) Oh and I guess I splet through an earthquake today, haha. One more for the to-do list complete.

Once again the Captains Crew stormed forward with another Most Spirited Award at Bellarmine's Relay for Life, making it three consecutive wins. There is already talk about creating a Crew Clan of sorts. Vi ska se....

anyhow, so now that Guatemala is done (minus awesome meetings on wednesday night) with and Relay is finished and I have a final list o school assignments, I can almost give a sign of relief that I'm about done. It's so close I can feel it dancing just outside of my fingertips. To graduate and be done with this silliness. My decisions of what to do change weekly, but regardless, I should have a nice summer of making money and enjoying myself. Much looking forward to it!!

Nothing else new in my book. About to start way early on homework to make the rest of this month easy (and because there is no longer a 360 here)

Hooray Spring might actually be here!!!

It's incredible how absolutely shitty I feel right now. Either a ghost is grabbing the hell out of my kidneys and squeeznig very very hard, or I'm being gutted. I really think running is out of the question today. Dammit.

Looks like a nap day. Amazing how that dissapoints me....:-(

Reading The time travelers wife makes me feel like I lose my grip on time. It also makes me think a lot about past mistakes, decisions, and where I'm going from here. I like the book, not always crazy about the feelings. 

I feel like I've been a lot heavier lately. Filled up with something and just pulled downward. I think it's responsible for the reason I've been so out of sync with myself lately. I'm hoping that I'm finally getting rid of that feeling, but part of it is lingering there and I just can't get my finger on it. I had some really deep thoughts on my bike ride home about life and where I'm going and my attitude. The only thing I remember is that I decided I want to have a better attitude, and in turn hopefully bring a better me to whatever I encounter. I'll write more as I think about it. 

I hope we keep this weather, the rain has been pissing me off. Today was wonderful to go riding in. 

I almost held the same kid twice this week. Almost being the important part. I'm quite certain he hates me, and I've gotten rather fond of that hatred. I think it really won't be long before I drop him. Tomorrow is looking doubtful as I get to make easter baskets. I do love the mindless work every so often, I think it's good for my sanity. 

So I'm looking for a new car....I'm also thinking about leaving the country, maybe helping children and wondering what the fuck I'm supposed to be doing with my life right now. I'm quite done with school, but I figure I'll go through the motions for cheap kicks. 

I'm losing my grip on being impressed with halo. It happened when I came back, and it's sad. I don't write (only in my head), i don't play video games or have ay hobbies reall because of how busy I've been. I just read. For right now that is enough, but when summer comes I'm going to need to figure out a way to keep myself entertained. 

I'm ramblingnow because I forgot all the deep and enlightening things. Sorry, maybe more later. 

***Life won't wait, live it now

Type your cut contents here. 
So I just finished the book blankets and got really depressed as a result. It is a graphic novel mostly about innoncence and finding our way with people by stumbling around in the dark. Anyhow it bothered me because I felt like i was looking back on a portrait of myself and realizing how little I appreciated having someone there for me when I really needed it. I think I've been scared for a long time and every time this has manifested itself in me, I'm shielded away from it. I feel like I've undervalued the people closest to me over time. I really don't like this. 

Life is a gigantic jumbled mess. Even in the midst of doing all the things I've gotten myself hooked into, I feel as if I'm not getting anywhere. I always have to be on a schedule, I never have free time for me. I just follow the courses of action that decide where I'm supposed to be and why. I really don't like this. I need a break where people aren't expecting something from me. Where friends don't want to hang out every night, where homework is not constantly catching up with me, or I'm slipping on my obligations to get work finished up for Guatemala or Relay. I need a few days away at the Abbey. I need to be isolated and reminded of who I am without the hundreds of strands of existance that are tied to me. 

I also have been getting mad at myself for not doing the things that I want to do. I don't have time to write the way I want to. I started too the other day and I erased it all because the form of it was terrible. I just felt so disconnected. Likewise, I can still have some basic conversation in swedish, but it's been difficult and I need to keep practicing, something I haven't had time for so far. I stopped running for almost a week and a half, and I haven't done anything to prepare myself for piano tomorrow. I really wish I could just get all of this shit together. 

I don't know where this came from, maybe a book or something, but yesterday I really had the urge to know how to stop caring. To be evil, not to have to feel anymore. I just want to be able to be completely selfish and not give a damn about what I am doing or how it affects the world around me. I've only dissasociated myself from everything twice. The idea of evil goes too far, but I think of it as just being selfish without feeling guilty about it. Freshman year and Sweden. The only two times I broke lose from things, was horribly self destructive and managed to survive somehow knowing a lot more about myself then I would have liked at times. 

In a few months I graduate. I don't know what the purpose or meaning for my life is. I'm not sure anyone does. It bothers me to an extent, but I am putting in an application at UofL, so I will have something to do with the the area of science that I'm interested in. I suppose that is something. I just wish I had something I could believe in that was pushing me. I feel rather listless right now and it's not very flattering. 

I miss my international friends. I hope May gets here soon so I get to see them...I really might cry when I see them. I need to get my tatoo when I have my tax return. 

I'm out of energy to keep writing. Hope all is well

I really don't know why I am having so much trouble right now. It almost makes me feel guilty that I've spent the last 25 minutes in class facebook stalking, reading livejournal, writing, or completely spacing off. The fact that I was five minutes late because I got coffee and a bear claw wasn't a factor in things either, he hadn't even started yet. I guess this is my reward for a lot of shit semesters and undue stress. It's like photography senior year of high school but easier. Just another 100 level class that the teacher puts everything online for me. Wow do I feel lazy now for picking this class. But no, certainly not guilty. Almost, but not quite.

I wonder if he would notice if I had headphones in...It's sort of a thing....WOW! I just asked a question about the northern lights. Woot there is my contribution today for class, he seemed excited that I asked.

The universe is somewhere around 14 billion years old. I don't think I can put into a comprehensible scale how incredibly small we are when presented against the rest of the universe. It kind of makes life seem pretty petty, makes all those problems and complaints with people and things seem pretty dumb...

Somewhere along the way recently I developed a temper. I don't know if it's because I work with a bunch of angry guys ready to kill me and I have to be assertive, if I'm bitter that I left part of my family in Sweden, or because life in general has found new and more creative ways to piss me off. I can't decide if I like it yet, but it's not the same it used to be. I'm sharper, but I feel like my edge is more jagged. It's almost like when I cut, I aim to hurt more, instead of trying to sugercoat or be soft on people. I feel like I've gotten my point across more.

I suck at articulating things. This pisses me off. Apparently I have a tendency to develop a personal meaning to words or sayings that others do not share. When I present it, and it's taken the wrong way, chaos insues. This blows, and I've decided that I don't like to try and articulate feelings because it will either be misunderstood or walked over forcibly to make me wrong. I don't want to argue with people, I don't want to fight, I just want them to fucking understand where I'm coming from without asserting their own meaning and feelings to trivialize my own.

If I don't find the discipline to write sometime soon, for like 4 hours, I might go crazy.

I have only been drunk twice I think so far this entire year. It's pretty exciting. I've only been hungover once, and it's only caused me to screw up one day of projects. I'm 4 months away from graduating and being done with college. Do I know if I want to do this work for the rest of my life? Do I know if this is the right path. Nope, and I don't care. If I change later in life, I'll find it in myself to change my path and do what i need too. I've almost finished college, most of the classes were pointless and gave me nothing of true worth, but it made me work for it. I've had to wake up early countless times, I've maintained a 3.0 and I've done a lot of stuff. People recognize that. They know as well as I that most of this stuff will never get used, but they recognize the committment I've made to an "idea" and they respect that because of a piece of paper. Does that bother me anymore? no. I've gotten used to the fact, and I don't care. I deserve their respect because I've earned it with something pointless. I hate to say it but that's life. You can earn a lot of respect by not doing anything but the bare minimal. If you can't give even that, don't expect to get recognition. I know some people don't agree with that, but unless they set out to change the system and suceed, their opinion really doesn't matter. They are just fighting against something they don't want to do in order to maintain a position they don't have the dedication to do anything about. Honestly I think that's worse then going along with it because you know it will get you somewhere in the end. Either fight and fail gloriously, or keep your values and do what it takes me make it count.

I've lost a sense of nobility. I still have my .....asked another question sorry. I have to feel like I'm doing something productive. it's a flaw. The next word was innocence, but I think romantic edge might be it too. I don't know why, but Ive lost my faith in it all. I'm reading a book on the american coup in Guatemala, and I just can't figure out how we can fight the people in power, how we can change such a vast and limitlessly powerful system. It makes me feel weak. People ask why we don't teach the people to work or farm down there. We can't. The system won't give them land or loan them money to help them. one little girl was going to die because her family couldn't afford to pay 2.75 to catch a bus to the nearest hospital. I spent $4 on breakfast this morning. how fucked up is that? Most people don't realize, most people don't care. But hey, even if it's not a huge lasting impression, we are building a health facility and school and that is the beginning of the change. Some people make the work charitable organizations do look petty because it's not some monsterous effort to change the world or bring about this awesome change. People like that piss me off because they sit and critisize what they do while they sit on their ass and pretend to be more self-rightoues, more knowledgable and worldly because they can verbally undermine the efforts of people who are doing what they can to make a difference. It's not much but at least it's something.

I don't think I'm strong enough to work for the Peace Corp. I get excited looking at it, but then I think about what it would really mean. Being gone for two years, being away from everything (in many ways would be a plus). I think of the good, but think about what I have to miss, what I have to give up and I get scared. I wish I was strong enough to know and not just put off the application in fear of what the oppurtunity could mean. I need to do three of those this weekend. I have the feeling I might end up somewhere random, just on the rare chance on being away from everything. I just typed most of this sentence and the last while looking at the board. I can even feel mistakes and fix them without looking. I'm getting too good at this. haha.

Long cons are amazing. They used one on Guatemala in the 50's to get the government overthrown. It was put on by the United Fruit Company. Not all the people were really evil, they were just ignorant of what was going on. They thought that the country was overrun with communist, because thats what they were afraid of. "Play on fear and everyone becomes your fool". Its part of the 1st rule. I wish I had the cunning and dark heart to play on this. Maybe I do and haven't realized it yet. Most people aren't bad, they are just ignorant and afraid. Is that bad? Of course it is, but how can combat ignorance without having to spend all day and night researching, or going to the sceen of everything, or throwing a rebellion. Which would be put down by the same people who think that the new ideas are fearful and don't know anything. Where do we draw the line to say who is the fool and who is worse because they think they are wise?

I think I'm done for now. Class is over, time for 2 hour lab. Hooray. Note the dripping sarcasm, please. Peace

I never knew that getting so much done could make me feel so tired. This semester I found something I was lacking before, a cause. Actually I found two, but lets not get too caught up in that. In a month in a half I'm going to Guatemala, and a month after that Bellarmine is having the annual Relay for Life. Needless to say I've put a lot on my plate when you look at working 25 a week, having three classes, piano lessons, and trying to write and learn a foriegn language (the latter two are suffering, but hopefully not for long). 

So I guess the reason I decided to put an entry in here is because I need to know what I'm doing. I'm in my last semester of undergrad (fingers crossed) and I already have a game plan for next year. I plan on making this a great semester and I plan on making my life different. I had a growing phase over the break and when it happened, I feel like I lost some of the innocence that was keeping me rooted in place. I'm growing more and more now. I feel more like an adult than I ever thought possible and it doesn't bother me anymore. I feel like I need this. 

Furthermore, I feel like I need to be here. Between Relay and Brooklawn, I know I can get a lot accomplished. I already talked to ACS (American Cancer Society) and if things don't work out for me here with psychology, I'm going to put something in to work with them. 

But somethings have happened that made me notice a change I don't feel quite as secure in. I feel like part of me has stopped feeling as accutely. Watching V for Vendetta and Rent really don't do anything for me. Fighting for freedom? Noble and great yeah, but we are no V's, I feel limited thinking about it, no matter how badass it is. Rent...no day but today? Why does it make me feel like some empty sound is echoing through me? It bothers me that something has changed in me, and I feel like I can't get that passion back. Is this what growing up is? Not knowing what or how to feel or what things mean to you anymore? It's almost like the knowledge that everything is relative and there because we want or need it to be has torn something apart in me. I don't like it. Yet I still persist in finding causes, something to do or something to fight for. 

I think thats why I'm like Jack in Lost. There are times where I make things happen, know what to do , know what to say to people to make it better and dive into it without thought or abandon, but that's the double edge sword. When that zeal gets misplaced, all that energy can get channeled into something that doesn't make sense, that once reflected on isn't as great idea as it seemed in the heat of the moment. Before, I've always needed something to fight for, as the girls were so fond of saying, I needed to be a hero. I'm well past being a hero, not like that. Those feelings broke in me. How can we come to terms with who we are if we don't have anything to gauge them from? Who am I? Who am I in the grander scheme of what is going on? What do I make of the power that I have, either given or taken? What will I do with it? The question of "What am I SUPPOSED to do with it" is no longer relavent to me.   

Questions, Questions, Questions. I'm not really confused. In fact I've never felt more in control of what I'm doing. The answers to the questons above helped me define who I am and what I'm doing. Because of them I feel determined and focused, stronger, ready to make things the way I want them to be without being anyone's "welcome mat" anymore. I'm done letting people do what they want with me because I won't stand up to it. If this is in my control, then it's going to be on my terms, all of it. I'm glad to see that I've come to realize this two weeks after I started living it. 

I may be a wreck, but at least I crash into what I'm aiming for.

So in recent news I got an iPod nano. I think I might be in love. 

This year was an overblown growing up experience. I feel like i was pushed all over the place, forxced to take positions and give them up just as readily, adapt quicker than I ever believed, and somehow make things work under the worst of curcimstances. In anothwer note, my spelling hasn't improved at all. In fact it might have gotten worse. 

I'm going out to the bars for news years tonight. It will be interesting. I'm expecting it to be a bit congested and crazy, add the effects of alcohol ad who knows what will happen. I predict all of us getting fed up with standing/getting bumped/slobered over and whatnot and leaving early. This is not to say I don't want to go. I feel like this is another thing everyone should do once, even if it ends terribly, just to say that it was done. I did another one of those things recently, but I really can't recall what it was now. I feel like it was somewhat important too. hmmmmm, I'll figure it out later. 

I'm really just killing time now because I don't have much else to do. I was pissed off for over an hour earlier today when I couldn't get our wireless router to work. I'm quite certain that the internet is messed up in the house now, and nothing I could do would fix it. So now we have nothing. I can't imagine Scott, Mom or Kevin being happy about that. hmmmm I'll call dad later. 

And Itunes is working, thank God I managed to get SOMETHING electronic to work today :-) :-) :-)

Story time. 

Gydar slipped away into darkness. Sometimes sleep had been a blessing, last night it had proven to be so, but now he was returning to a place he had once let go. Lights, without warning swam around him and he was standing before a large black door. He felt something, almost pain in his left arm, and he didn't need to look down to see know what was waiting for him on the other side. It had finally returned, the only one he had yet to bury. Was it time? His left arm, decorated with black spirals and designs went to the hilt of his sword. He had grown so much in such a short period of time, but he was so tired now, so so tired. 

The great wooden doors opened as if my an invisable hand and he forced himself to step forward boldly, if he was to fall, it would be gloriously, not like some coward in the corner of a cell. Striding forward into the the arena he lifted his blade from his belt and with great pain held it before him in his left hand. It was waiting for him. Without age or sex, the demon stood ready as it had years and times before, for the dance. Gydar's face remained impassive, he would not give the monster the satisfactiion of knowing he was scarred to death. Slowly, he removed the blade from the scabbard, twilit colors flooded the dim arena in a pale light. When it touched the demon, it fell back in suprise. 

"You are a fool O'Murkin." The voice was a hiss, like a snake trying to speak and the demons body semed to mimic it's nature as it swayed back and forth. 

"I'm well aware, but I am no coward. You will kill me now, or you will fail. I will not live a poisened life in your shadow." As if in the answer, the blackness, the darkness on his arms flared into pain, reminding him of the cost he was to pay. 

The demon slithered forward, a twisted smile creeping upon it's face. "You will fall again. You have never had the strength to break my hold, and now is still not yet that day."

Gydar gave a bitter smile. He was well past a place of caring what happened to him. He lauched himself forward as twilight sang and the dance was begun.

"We will see"

I don't know how I feel yet about brining back stories into things. I guess since I update this so little anyway it doesn't matter. I think I'm going to start doing this again just for writing practice with the real story tiself. Not that anyone cares to read that, but hey, in the end it's for me I suppose. I just feel like it would be a shame not to give so much energy and imagination true life through coherant writing. 

I worked for 13 hours yesterday. I came home and slept for a solid 10 and 1/2 hours without waking. I think it might have been the best sleep of my life. 

I really wish someone could cover my shift tomorrow, but it looks like I have to see the nutcracker. Yeah it does sound fun, until you factor in the 1-2 dozen children that have behavioral problems that I will be with and the fact that it's three hours long give or take and every extra minute it takes me is one more I don't get to see my dad and visit for christmas. So quite frustrating really, but hey, that seems to be life, right? 

I feel bad because I haven't seen many people lately, but I'm not terribly upset because I feel like I really need a break from life. Part of the reason I'm glad to go see dad is because Owensboro is almost completely cut off from life here. I might just turn my phone off while I'm there. I just need a break from everything, and when I'm at work and get more than a dozen text messages and calls to hang out, but can't turn off the phone since work needs to call me if problems arise too, I get upset. Maybe I can salvage something out of this break. At least, thats what I'm hoping. 

The bad thing about sleeping in is that I don't have a whole lot of time to get things done before work. As it is I'll be there until 8-9 again tonight, but hey, I do need the money. 

I probably won't make another entry before, so Merry Christmas and Happy New Year!

I feel like I'm losing my mind right now. It's the same old crap. I don't like school, I don't know what I am going to do next year, and even worse I don't know what i WANT to do. Well I do, but I don't know how to go about writing crap and sustaining myself with activism. 

I don't know why I'm so depressive right now, I guess I'm just one a short leash and thinking too much about all these stupid fucking assignments that are due on monday and tuesday. Serisouly teachers, you aren't the only clever ones who think you can get some extra grading in over the holidays. How about you manage your fucking time a little better so we don't have to fuck our own schedules and turn in shit. At the least, don't pretend to be dissapointed in us, both parties know you probbaly give less a damn than we do. 

Wow I'm bitter. Maybe it will help me study, haha. At least I'm going to guatemala now, but even that feels weird, and I haven't quite figured out why. 

If I can stop sabotaging myself, I'm going to run a marathon in April. Wish me luck

3 and 1/2 days until SOA, yaysa!
I am determined to make these dreams come to pass.

I came to a heavy conclusion while I was abroad. Actually, it was more of common sense, but it was profound enough to me for me to re-think what I was going to do. I decided that if I want something, I mean really want something, I will be willing to do whatever it takes to get it done. When you REALLY want something, you get it, because that's all there is. 

This is the problem, I don't know what I want. For next year at least. I just dont know. So how can I work towards something that isn't there yet? hmmmm.....

But to be a total geek, it is national write a novel month or something. So I think I'm going to try and get on that, or just get it started if nothing else. We will see...

We have all been sucked and pulled into a gigantic game that has no meaning or purpose. Unlike real games, there is no overseeer, there is no all knowing being watching our every move. It's just what it is, a game. The scores don't matter, we really don't even matter beyond ourselves, but we still play it for someone else, as if to claim our lives aren't worth being lived as they are. 

I would say it is good that I'm learning this now. Had I learned it any earlier, I don't think I would have been on this track to finish school.....:-) But in saying that, I show how much of the problem I really have become. Regardless, I'm ready to be done, I don't feel like I'm being taught anything about real life. Theories and ideas and bullshit. We need the next philosophical age to be here now. Otherwsie, I fear for what humanity could become.  

So what now...

Ender'a Game is a horribly negative influence to helping me fit into a box. I'm glad I had the free time and an awesome girlfriend to get me into it.

Light up, light up, as if you have a choice. 

I love music. It makes me feel.......things i can't explain. It sends me far away, and even if it borders on grief or sadness, it makes me smile and feel right again. 

There really is so little point to doing this work right now. So close, so close to.......

The difference between a disaster and an adventure is how you describe it. 

There is only us, there is only this, forget regret or life is yours to miss. 

until I fall away, I won't keep you waiting long. 

until next time....

I think I was supposed to get mono right now. 

When I got back, I really didn't give myself any time to process anything, the having left for sweden, coming back, the changes I felt and went through, I just pushed through it out of habit. I think I might have been afraid to look at things with the change. Trying to adapt myself and my surrondings to new ways of feeling and seeing things. I guess it's why I never got mono before. It needed to be now. 

Not that I've had a great deal of time to reflect. I've been so f-ing exhausted by just walking upstairs, and going to class yesterday sucked the life out of me. I think when someone really doesn't want to deal with a situation, they truely can find a million ways of getting around it. Explains why I haven't written anything lately either. hmm.....

I need to make sure I don't sail right back into auto-pilot, there are too many things I have been missing or messing up because I was too busy getting from point a to point c.

Things might get difficult soon, but I supposed I should be thankful, if they weren't difficult, I'd get way too bored

Fuck Mono. that is all

excpet that when he told me I started laughing, went to school, then to work, to clear everything up, and still had to go to physicals tonight, because bellarmine has its head so far up it's ass it can't plan for shit, nor be understanding. 

But I have the week off, and don't feel the mono is sucking my entire energy supply away mentality so I tihnk I will finally get to play catch up on everything life. Ha, we will see how that goes. 

Time to play with the new baby, which is my laptop.

I had my last day of lessons yesterday, for some reason, I thought this was important. Probably because I'm happy they are done

School starts in 3 weeks. I have 9 books for two classes, yay!

Grad school, internship, GRE, 16 hours, a life....... I'm a little uncertain when and where all of this is going to take place. 

Harry Potter was fantastically awesome. 

I started a chapter today on Bryce. It is rather difficult. In fact, writing for me in general is pretty tough. I don't feel like my words can suffice to give justice to everything I wish it could be. But this is the farthest I have ever gone with something like this......vi ska se. 

Jag bara skriv lite svenska. Jag missa det.

Right now, I feel exhausted. 

Somewhere between the reverse culture shock. The missing knowing what is going on too an almost disturbing levels with the drama and everyday occurances of a dozen very special international people. Starting to work full time. Moving everything to the basement where I am taking over. My phone not being silent for more than 20 minutes on average (when I was used to not getting a call for days, because we had messenger). MESSENGER NOT WORKING AND BEING PISSED ABOUT IT. David not being back (you whore). 

I am worn out, stretched, and still very much adjusting to this new (yes....new) life. I don't want to revert to things before, and I don't think I have.
